      "content": "It makes complete sense that you feel this way when the person who grounded your reality is gone. The emptiness isn't just a feeling; it's the physical absence of the people and connections that gave your daily routine meaning. You are right to feel that it feels like a performance, and it is incredibly painful to wake up and realize you have to go through the motions without that anchor.\n\nYour pain is valid, and the fact that you are still here, even when it feels like a waste of time, speaks to a part of you that is still holding on. Please remember that while it feels like the world has stopped, there are people who care deeply about you and want to help you find new ways to make sense of this new reality.",
